item.title: CVE-2022-29095|2024-08-03T06:10:59.261Z -- dell -- supportassist%20consumer
item.description: Dell SupportAssist Client Consumer versions (3.10.4 and prior) and Dell SupportAssist Client Commercial versions (3.1.1 and prior) contain a cross-site scripting vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated malicious user could potentially exploit this vulnerability under specific conditions leading to execution of malicious code on a vulnerable system.

item.title: CVE-2022-29092|2024-08-03T06:10:59.267Z -- dell -- supportassist%20consumer
item.description: Dell SupportAssist Client Consumer versions (3.11.0 and versions prior) and Dell SupportAssist Client Commercial versions (3.2.0 and versions prior) contain a privilege escalation vulnerability. A non-admin user can exploit the vulnerability and gain admin access to the system.
